<p>It is known that we'll use two dotted lines to express two lines are perpendicular (like the picture).</p>  <p>Is there any argument to express this symbol such as <code>symbol="perpendicular"</code>? </p>  <p>So far, I plot this symbol manually like code below.</p>  <pre><code>plot(rnorm(10),type="n",xlim=c(-1,1),ylim=c(-1,1)) abline(h=0,v=0) lines(c(0,0.1),c(0.1,0.1),lty=2) lines(c(0.1,0.1),c(0,0.1),lty=2) </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/U8Ijy.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/U8Ijy.jpg" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>